article.headline: Ole Miss continues mastery of Arkansas behind Goff's 18
article.linkText: Ole Miss cruises to 7th straight win vs. Arkansas
article.story:
OXFORD, Miss, (AP) -- Shawn Goff had 18 points, nine rebounds, and three blocked shots to help Mississippi upset Arkansas (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) 63-55 on Sunday.

Mississippi (7-8, 1-1 Southeastern Conference) has beat Arkansas in seven straight games and hasn't lost to the Razorbacks in 12 meetings in Oxford.

Arkansas (15-2, 0-2) was playing without Lauren Ervin, the team's leading scorer, who will miss the rest of the season with a torn anterior cruciate ligament. Ervin averaged 16 points and 11 rebounds. She hurt her right knee Thursday night in the Lady Razorbacks' 76-54 loss to No. 11 LSU.

Elizabeth Robertson and Kayla Melson both added 12 points for the Rebels and Carla Bartee scored 11 points.

Brittney Vaughn led Arkansas with 15 points, Whitney Jones scored 13 and Sarah Pfeifer and Charity Ford both chipped in 10.

Arkansas was down 31-18 at halftime, but managed to close the gap to 34-30 with a 10-3 run early in the second half.

It was the first conference win for new Ole Miss coach Renee Ladner.
